    summary: 'This evaluation study examines the outcomes of Bioversity International\'s collaboration with the MS Swaminathan Research Foundation to promote minor millets in India through participatory research, conservation, and value chain development. The study analyzes the impact of interventions on millet production, consumption, and income in two study locations over an 11-year period (2007-2018), while also examining the potential effects of India\'s National Food Security Act of 2013 which mandated millets as a scheduled commodity in the public distribution system.',
