    summary: 'This is a comprehensive academic review that synthesizes current knowledge on Fusarium wilt of banana, a devastating soil-borne disease caused by Fusarium oxysporum f. sp. cubense (Foc). The review addresses critical knowledge gaps in disease epidemiology and proposes integrated management approaches for sustainable disease control, with particular focus on the emerging tropical race 4 (TR4) strain that threatens global banana production.',
    what_it_does: 'The review synthesizes existing knowledge on Fusarium wilt epidemiology, identifies research gaps, and proposes integrated management strategies combining exclusion, resistant cultivars, soil health practices, and biological control approaches.',
